cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.DB, cs.CL, cs.SOC

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category as it deals with the analysis of social networks using Twitter data. It could also belong to cs.SD (Software Development) as it discusses the design and implementation of a multi-terabyte relational database. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.DB (Databases) as it deals with database design and loading procedures. The paper also discusses linguistic analysis of tweets, which could place it under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, since the paper focuses on the geographic features of social networks, it could be categorized under cs.SOC (Social and Community Informatics).
